# Testing Guide

## Run tests

```bash
php artisan test                        # full suite (165+ tests)
php artisan test --filter ClassName     # single class
php artisan test --stop-on-failure      # stop on first failure (used in deploy)
```

Tests use **SQLite in-memory** (configured in `phpunit.xml`). No Docker needed.

---

## Structure

```
tests/
  Unit/          # pure logic, no HTTP — Services, Jobs, helpers
  Feature/       # HTTP requests via actingAs() — Web controllers
  Feature/Api/   # JSON endpoints — API controllers (X-API-Key auth)

database/factories/  # Eloquent factories for every model
```

---

## Unit test (Service / pure logic)

Use `Tests\TestCase` + `RefreshDatabase` when DB is needed.
Mock external dependencies with `$this->createMock()`.

```php
class MyServiceTest extends TestCase
{
    use RefreshDatabase;

    public function test_it_does_something(): void
    {
        $dep = $this->createMock(ExternalService::class);
        $dep->expects($this->once())->method('call')->willReturn('ok');

        $service = new MyService($dep);
        $result  = $service->doSomething();

        $this->assertEquals('ok', $result);
    }
}
```

---

## Testing Jobs (Queue)

Use `Queue::fake()` to intercept dispatches without actually running them.

```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Queue;
use App\Jobs\MyJob;

public function test_action_dispatches_job(): void
{
    Queue::fake();

    // trigger the action that dispatches the job
    $service->doSomething();

    Queue::assertPushed(MyJob::class);
    Queue::assertNotPushed(OtherJob::class);

    // Assert with constraints on the job
    Queue::assertPushed(MyJob::class, function ($job) use ($bot) {
        return in_array('bot:' . $bot->id, $job->tags());
    });
}
```

**ShouldBeUnique jobs**: `Queue::fake()` bypasses the uniqueness lock, so duplicate-dispatch tests work normally in tests.

