## Testing GridTradingEngine with mocked Binance

`GridTradingEngine` requires `BinanceFuturesService` which calls external APIs.
Minimal mock setup: create a bot with **no orders** so `syncOrderStatuses` and
`handleFilledOrders` return early. Only `getPositions` (for `updateBotStats`) and
`getCurrentPrice` (for `checkStopConditions`) need stubbing.

```php
use App\Services\BinanceFuturesService;
use App\Services\GridTradingEngine;
use App\Repositories\BotRepository;
use App\Repositories\OrderRepository;
use App\Services\GridCalculatorService;

class MyEngineTest extends TestCase
{
    use RefreshDatabase;

    private GridTradingEngine $engine;
    private BinanceFuturesService $binanceMock;

    protected function setUp(): void
    {
        parent::setUp();

        $this->binanceMock = $this->createMock(BinanceFuturesService::class);
        $this->binanceMock->method('getPositions')->willReturn([]);  // for updateBotStats

        $this->engine = new GridTradingEngine(
            $this->binanceMock,
            app(BotRepository::class),
            app(OrderRepository::class),
            app(GridCalculatorService::class),
        );
    }

    public function test_something_when_price_hits_condition(): void
    {
        Queue::fake();

        $bot = Bot::factory()->active()->create(['stop_loss_price' => 79000.0]);
        $this->binanceMock->method('getCurrentPrice')->willReturn(78000.0);

        $this->engine->processBot($bot);

        Queue::assertPushed(RunAgentAlertJob::class);
        $bot->refresh();
        $this->assertEquals(BotStatus::Active, $bot->status); // not stopped!
    }
}
```

**Key**: bot with no orders = `syncOrderStatuses` returns early (no `binance_order_id`),
`handleFilledOrders` returns early (no filled orders), `autoRebuildIfEmpty` returns early
(no filled orders). Only `getPositions` and `getCurrentPrice` need mocking.

