## Spy pattern — assert a method is NEVER called

Use `getMockBuilder()->onlyMethods()` to create a spy that verifies a method
is not invoked (useful to guard against regressions like "stopBot never called directly"):

```php
$spy = $this->getMockBuilder(GridTradingEngine::class)
    ->setConstructorArgs([
        $this->binanceMock,
        app(BotRepository::class),
        app(OrderRepository::class),
        app(GridCalculatorService::class),
    ])
    ->onlyMethods(['stopBot'])
    ->getMock();

$spy->expects($this->never())->method('stopBot');

$spy->processBot($bot); // if stopBot is called internally, test fails
```

