## Manual testing in localhost (Docker)

For testing agent flows end-to-end in local environment:

```bash
# Simulate SL/TP alert → agent consultation (synchronous, shows result)
docker compose exec laravel.test php artisan bot:test-alert {botId}
docker compose exec laravel.test php artisan bot:test-alert {botId} --type=tp

# Run the scheduler manually
docker compose exec laravel.test php artisan schedule:run

# Dispatch all active bot processing jobs manually
docker compose exec laravel.test php artisan queue:work --once
```

After running `bot:test-alert`, view the conversation at `/ai-agent/conversations/{id}`.

