## Checklist for new feature / update

- [ ] New Service method → Unit test covering happy path + edge cases
- [ ] New web route → Feature test: auth required, 403 for other users, success case
- [ ] New API endpoint → Feature/Api test: 401 without key, 403 on ownership, 200 success
- [ ] New model → factory with `use HasFactory` on the model
- [ ] Job that dispatches conditionally → `Queue::fake()` + `assertPushed`/`assertNotPushed`
- [ ] Action that logs to `bot_action_logs` → `assertDatabaseHas('bot_action_logs', [...])`
- [ ] Critical guard (e.g. "never call stopBot directly") → spy test with `expects($this->never())`
- [ ] Agent behavior change → test with correct trigger (`scheduled`/`manual`/`sl_tp_alert`)
- [ ] Run `composer stan` — PHPStan must return `[OK] No errors`
- [ ] Run `php artisan test` — all tests must pass before committing

## PHPStan (static analysis)

```bash
composer stan          # ./vendor/bin/phpstan analyse --memory-limit=512M
composer lint          # ./vendor/bin/pint --test  (code style)
composer check         # stan + lint + tests together
```

If a new `selectRaw` / `withCount` pattern produces `property.notFound` that's a framework-dynamic false positive (not a real bug), update the baseline:

```bash
./vendor/bin/phpstan analyse --memory-limit=512M --generate-baseline=phpstan-baseline.neon
```

Do NOT add `@phpstan-ignore` to silence real type errors — fix the code.
